  "prompt": "Who has been most prolific Indian Chief of Army Staff?",
  "response": "The most prolific Indian Chief of Army Staff in terms of tenure is General K. Sundarji. He served as the Chief of Army Staff from 1986 to 1988. He is often recognized for his role in modernizing the Indian Army and for his leadership during significant military operations, including the Indian Peace Keeping Force (IPKF) deployment in Sri Lanka. \n\nHowever, if you are referring to the longest-serving Chief of Army Staff, that title goes to General K. M. Cariappa, who served from 1949 to 1953, being the first person to hold the position.\n\nEach Chief of Army Staff has had their own unique impact on the Indian Army's development, operational readiness, and strategic direction.",
